h1. ui:fieldErrors

h2. Purpose

Specifies custom markup for the errors part of a @ui:field@ rendering.

h2. Example

{code:xml}
<ui:field bean="${form}" name="${beastNumber}">
	<ui:fieldErrors>
		<g:if test="${form.beastNumber != 666}">
			This is the wrong number for the beast!
		</g:if>
	</ui:fieldErrors>
</ui:field>
{code}

h2. Attributes

None. The body is used as the label content for the outer [field|uiTags] tag.
